 The state Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Delta State, Elder Omeni Sobotiehe, has described the Executive Director, Nigerian Export Import Bank (NEXIM), Hon Stella Okotete, as an amazon and an invaluable asset to the party, state and Nigeria. In a statement congratulating the former National Women Leader on her re-appointment, the party stated that she has indeed acquitted herself as altogether a true Amazon and invaluable asset to the APC. According to him, the re-appointment was well deserving in the light of her sterling qualities and thanked the President for finding her worthy. The statement reads in parts: ” On behalf of the State Executive Committee, the leadership of the party, and the entire party faithful, I most heartily congratulate Hon. Stella Okotete on her well-deserved reappointment as Executive Director (Business Development), NEXIM Bank, by our dear President, Commander-in-Chief, Muhammadu Buhari. “While we are most grateful to His Excellency for this great honour done to our dear state, Hon. Okotete’s reappointment is not at all surprising, in light of her sterling stewardship throughout her first term in office. “We therefore happily join scores of her well-wishers and admirers in celebrating this renewed opportunity accorded her to continue in service to the nation by Mr. President. ‘Hon. Okotete’s career in politics and service to humanity thus, far, have been most commendable and, indeed, worthy of note. “As party stalwart, grassroots mobilizer, banking executive and National Women Leader, Hon. Okotete has only brought pride and joy to our great party and dear state. “She has indeed acquitted herself as altogether a true Amazon and invaluable asset to our great party. “Needless to say, we remain cast iron confident in her capacity to deliver once again and, make us proud, once more, even as she has always done before. “